title: Room-Description Snippets (ADR-209)
story: concealment-test
description: End-to-end splice pass - cycling variants, save/restore counters, mentions gate, duplicate markers, initial/standard shared counters

---

# --- AC-9: initialDescription and description share the clock counter ---
# First look = first visit = initialDescription, clock pick 1.
> look
[OK: contains "You step into a quiet study"]
[OK: contains "A grandfather clock ticks softly in the corner."]

# Second look = standard description, clock pick 2 (shared counter advanced).
> look
[OK: contains "A quiet study with heavy curtains"]
[OK: contains "The grandfather clock ticks away, unhurried."]

# --- Reach the parlor ---
> north
[OK: contains "Hall"]

# --- AC-1 shape: first parlor render — fixed cabinet entry, mantel pick 1,
# duplicate dust marker resolving identically at both sites (AC-8),
# trunk mention present (gate open).
> east
[OK: contains "Parlor"]
[OK: contains "doorway to the west, next to a cabinet"]
[OK: contains "fireplace, the mantel holding sentimental items."]
[OK: contains "Thick dust coats the shelves; Thick dust hangs in the air."]
[OK: contains "A battered trunk sits in the corner."]

# --- AC-2: cycling advances in declaration order; dust flips together (AC-8) ---
> look
[OK: contains "next to a cabinet"]
[OK: contains "fireplace, its mantel crowded with keepsakes."]
[OK: contains "Thin dust coats the shelves; Thin dust hangs in the air."]

# --- AC-3: save mid-cycle ---
$save snippets-mid-cycle

# mantel pick 3; dust wraps back to Thick.
> look
[OK: contains "fireplace, a few sentimental items on the mantel."]
[OK: contains "Thick dust coats the shelves; Thick dust hangs in the air."]

# AC-2: mantel wraps to pick 1.
> look
[OK: contains "fireplace, the mantel holding sentimental items."]

# --- AC-3: restore — the cycle resumes where the save left it ---
$restore snippets-mid-cycle

> look
[OK: contains "fireplace, a few sentimental items on the mantel."]
[OK: contains "Thick dust coats the shelves; Thick dust hangs in the air."]

# --- AC-4: the mentions gate follows the trunk (Q9: transitive containment) ---
# Carry the trunk out of the parlor and leave it in the hall.
> take trunk
[OK: contains "Taken"]

> west
[OK: contains "Hall"]

> drop trunk
[OK: contains "Dropped"]

# Trunk elsewhere: its sentence evaporates; everything else still splices.
> east
[OK: contains "Parlor"]
[OK: contains "next to a cabinet"]
[OK: not contains "A battered trunk sits in the corner."]

# Bring it home: the mention resumes (AC-4, entity returns).
> west
[OK: contains "Hall"]

> take trunk
[OK: contains "Taken"]

> east
[OK: contains "Parlor"]

> drop trunk
[OK: contains "Dropped"]

> look
[OK: contains "A battered trunk sits in the corner."]
